headline: Starbucks Beefs Up CEO Security Spending
summary: Starbucks has hiked its spending on security for Chief Executive Brian Niccol, saying his profile has risen and the “threat landscape” has become more concerning.  The coffee chain spent around $1.1 million on security for Niccol in the fiscal year ended Sept. 28.  Security spending was about $128,000 in the prior year, when Niccol started in the role.

headline: Starbucks Removes Limits for CEO's Private Jet Use Over Security Concerns
summary: Under the travel agreement, which was altered following a security review, Niccol no longer has to pay Starbucks back for non-professional use of the jet, according to a filing.  Previously, he was responsible for charges from personal travel after an annual cap of $250,000.
